I've been diving down the shadow work rabbit hole lately and stumbled upon this podcast that has actually caused a couple "ah hah" moments for me in terms of why I am the way I am. She explains and expands on Carl Jung's concept of shadow and explains things in a relatable (not so dry) way that's helped me wrap my head around what I personally used to just write off as unexplainable or unknown or "just the way things are". I'm trying to take accountability and practice radical acceptance to let go of what's keeping me in this self destructive cycle and I can't help but feel some folks here are going through a similar cycle. 

Anyways, if I get one person turned on to this and help them realign their perspective- this won't have been for nothing. (Caution, shadow work and diving into your subconscious is heavy shit, so be prepared to look in the mirror before embarking)

Enjoy!
